did.head: Summary Information
did.abstract: The United World Federalists mss., 1928-1988, consists of correspondence and internal memoranda; records relating to the United World Federalists's history, organization, policies and programs, committee reports, student chapters, general assemblies held annually in different cities; financial accounts and membership records; and manuals and other publications issued by the national office on a variety of issues.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The United World Federalists was a non-partisan, non-profit organization with members in forty-eight states. This organization was founded in Asheville, North Carolina on February 23, 1947 as the result of a merger of five existing world government groups: Americans United for World Government; World Federalists, U.S.A.; Student Federalists; Georgia World Citizens Committee; and the Massachusetts Committee for World Federation. The organization became World Federalists, USA in the 1960s, before changing its name again in the 1970s to World Federalists Association.

The primary purpose of the organization is: (1) to achieve permanent peace through universal disarmament enforced by law; (2) to release for the satisfaction of human needs the resources that at present must be used in continuous preparation for war; (3) to maintain and promote human freedom, and to mobilize support for free institutions among all peoples; (4) to secure to all peoples the right to develop according to their own customs and traditions. Based entirely in the United States it is one of the largest member organizations of the World Federalist Movement. While the two organizations work closely together on many programs they are incorporated separately, with separate staffs, headquarters, and governing boards.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The arrangement and contents of the files have been retained and listed as received.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of correspondence and internal memoranda; records relating to the United World Federalists's history, organization, policies and programs, committee reports, student chapters, general assemblies held annually in different cities; financial accounts and membership records; and manuals and other publications issued by the national office on a variety of issues. In addition there are scrapbooks, audio tapes, films and phonograph albums.

controlaccess.head: Indexing Terms
controlaccess.p: The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in IUCAT, the IU Libraries' online catalog. Materials about related topics, persons or places can be found by searching the catalog using these terms.

userestrict.head: Usage Restrictions
userestrict.p: Prior arrangements are not necessary before coming to the Library, however, patrons from out of town are encouraged to communicate with the Library in advance of their visits to ascertain availability of materials.
Photocopying permitted only with permission of the Curator of Manuscripts, Lilly Library.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Item], United World Federalists mss., Lilly Library, Indiana University, Bloomington, Indiana.

scopecontent.p: Boxes 1-7 consist of correspondence, membership reports, chapter reports, membership lists, announcements for meetings, newsletters, newspaper clippings, minutes of meetings
